The objective method [4] starts by identifying studies either by scanning the references of similar, already published systematic reviews, or by issuing broad queries to medical databases (e.g., PubMed, MEDLINE) and screening a subset for identifying gold-standard references. These references form the ‘test’ set, which is divided into a development set (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
